M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 weakly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 204-206
) 0.66-0.75 mm long, symmetrical, strongly sclerotized. Apical process of median lobe robust, inflexed, with almost oblique ventral side, blunt apex. Articular process robust, not prominent. Parameres with strongly widened bases and each with large, curved lobe, in dorsal view evenly wide and almost evenly curved, excepted in basal section. Internal sac with a pair of conspicuous, strongly sclerotized rods joined by V-shaped apophysis and complex basal sclerites, membranous denticulate structures present in basal part only.
